Package: pylink
Architecture: all
Depends: ${python3:Depends},
         ${misc:Depends},
         python3-ircmatch,
         python3-yaml
Recommends: python3-expiringdict, python3-passlib
Suggests: pylink-doc
Enhances: inspircd, ircd-ratbox, charybdis, ircd-hybrid
Description: Multi-network IRC Services & server-side relayer
 PyLink is an extensible, plugin-based IRC services framework written in
 Python. It aims to be:
 .
 1) a replacement for the now-defunct Janus.
 .
 2) a versatile framework and gateway to IRC.

Package: pylink-doc
Section: doc
Architecture: all
Depends: ${misc:Depends},
Description: Multi-network IRC Services & server-side relayer (extra docs)
 PyLink is an extensible, plugin-based IRC services framework written in
 Python. It aims to be:
 .
 1) a replacement for the now-defunct Janus.
 .
 2) a versatile framework and gateway to IRC.
 .
 This package provides a Doxygen-generated API reference for PyLink IRC
 Services.
